      "description": "One-loop triangle penguin with charged scalar $\\eta^+$ (mass $m_1=m_\\eta$) on two edges and Majorana fermion $N_i$ (mass $m_2=m_{N_i}$) on the third edge, mediating $\\ell_\\alpha \\to \\ell_\\beta \\gamma$ and the photon/Z-penguin contribution to $\\ell_\\alpha \\to 3 \\ell_\\beta$ in the scotogenic model. External lepton momenta and masses are neglected, so only the dimensionless ratio $\\xi_i = m_{N_i}^2/m_\\eta^2$ enters. The form factors are projected onto the dipole loop function $F_2(x)=(1-6x+3x^2+2x^3-6x^2 \\log x)/(6(1-x)^4)$ and the non-dipole monopole loop function $G_2(x)=(2-9x+18x^2-11x^3+6x^3 \\log x)/(6(1-x)^4)$, given in closed rational+log form in Appendix A. Both are finite ($\\varepsilon^0$).",
